-- Turkey to Drill for Oil Around North Cyprus, Sabah Says
-- B y   B e n j a m i n   H a r v e y
-- 2012-04-08T17:00:26Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-08/turkey-to-drill-for-oil-around-north-cyprus-sabah-says.html
Turkish state-owned oil exploration
firm Türkiye Petrolleri Anonim Ortakligi, or TPAO, will begin
drilling for oil in the waters near northern Cyprus, Sabah
newspaper  reported  the energy minister as saying.  The drilling will begin “when ministers return from a
visit to China” on April 11, Sabah reported Energy Minister
 Taner Yildiz  as saying.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Benjamin Harvey in Istanbul at 
 bharvey11@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Gavin Serkin at   gserkin@bloomberg.net  